  <a href="#1" id="1">
   President Bush has named career diplomat Deane Hinton as ambassador to Panama, the White House announced Tuesday, 01/02/1990.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   Hinton, currently ambassador to Costa Rica, replaces Ambassador Arthur H. Davis.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   Bush named Hinton as a recess appointment because Congress is not in session.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   That means Hinton can serve until the end of next year before he must go before the Senate for confirmation.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   The appointment of the 66-year-old Hinton, with his long expierience on Latin American issues, is seen as a signal of the importance Bush is placing on restoring normal relations with Panama.
  </a>
